# WIP Raspberry Pi 4 Installation Log - v4
# Date: 2025-01-31
# Target: Raspberry Pi 4 (2GB RAM) with Caddy/OIDC

## Prerequisites

### 1. Enable Unprivileged Ports for Rootless Podman

Caddy needs ports 80 and 443. Rootless Podman can't bind to ports < 1024 by default.

**Fix (required before running pi-setup.sh):**
```bash
echo 'net.ipv4.ip_unprivileged_port_start=80' | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf
sudo sysctl -p
```

This persists across reboots.

### 2. Podman Registry Configuration

Ensure docker.io is configured:
```bash
grep -q 'docker.io' /etc/containers/registries.conf || \
  echo 'unqualified-search-registries = ["docker.io"]' | sudo tee -a /etc/containers/registries.conf
```

## Installation Steps

```bash
# 1. Download setup script
curl -O http://192.168.1.17:3000/peter/World-In-A-Pie/raw/branch/main/scripts/pi-setup.sh

# 2. Run setup (full mode with Caddy/OIDC)
bash pi-setup.sh

# Or minimal mode (API keys only, no Caddy):
bash pi-setup.sh --minimal
```

## Deployment Modes

| Mode | Containers | Auth | Access | RAM |
|------|------------|------|--------|-----|
| Full | MongoDB, PostgreSQL, NATS, Dex, Caddy + 6 services | OIDC + API keys | https://hostname | ~1GB |
| Minimal | MongoDB, PostgreSQL, NATS + 6 services | API keys only | http://hostname:3000 | ~900MB |

